CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 6, 1955, pg. 11, reads: "Min-Ceil Guests - Among the guests were several out-of-towners at the fashionable Min-Ceil Club breakfast. Seated, left to right; Mrs. Olive Tate of Greensboro, M.C., and Miss Mollie Faison of Detroit, Mich.  Standing in same order: Dr. J.D. Avent of Tallahassee, Fla; Mrs. Roland Benjamin and Roland Benjamin, New York; Mrs. Bertie Weathers, Columbia, S.C., and Mrs. J. D. Avent, Tallahassee.  Mrs. Mary Reid Johnson was also at the event but is not pictured.-Teenie Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of two men and five women, left to right seated; Olive Tate, Mollie Faison, standing; Dr. J.D. Avent, Mrs. Roland Benjamin, Mr. Roland Benjamin, Bertie Weathers, and Mrs. J.D.Avent, out of town guests gathered in front of Emmett F. Davises home for Min-Ceil Club breakfast
